      • getHoughSpaceSizeAndGenerateLUT

        public int[] getHoughSpaceSizeAndGenerateLUT(int imageWidth,
                                             int imageHeight)
        The parametric equation for a circle centered at (a,b) with radius r is: a = x - r*cos(theta) b = y - r*sin(theta) In order to speed calculations, we first construct a lookup table (lut) containing the rcos(theta) and rsin(theta) values, for theta varying from 0 to 2*PI with increments equal to: 1/pointsOfReference*radiusMax. Return value = Number of angles for each radius
